# UI Polish Tweaks

## Global Design Rules
- Remove borders from UI elements unless strictly required (e.g., input active states).

## Top Row (Left)
- Remove border and background color from Song and Show dropdowns ("naked" dropdowns).
- Ensure dropdown chevron matches the selected text color.

## Top Row (Right)
- Redundant "playback state" text removed.
- **Server Chip:** Always displays "SERVER". Uses background color for state (🟢 OPEN/Green, 🟡 CONNECTING/Yellow, 🔴 CLOSED/Red).
- **Live Drift Gauge:** 4em wide, 2px red bar originating from center `0`. Left = negative drift, right = positive drift. Overlay white text with the ms value.
- **State Chip:** Displays state text. Background green if READY/PLAYING. Gray for IDLE/other.

## Waveform Area
- Remove the encompassing border from the wavesurfer container.
- **Scrollbar:** Custom 0.5em scrollbar track (black track, gray thumb).

## Playback Controls
- Icon-only transport (remove text from buttons).
- Combine Play and Pause into a single toggle button.
- Make the Play/Pause button 0.25em larger than Load/Stop.

## Bottom Area (3 Columns)
- Remove the borders from the 3 column containers (Diagnostics, DMX Monitor, Event Log).
- Allow the columns to expand and use all remaining vertical height.
- Add an auto-hiding vertical scrollbar to each column independently if their content overflows.
